87fb/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-04-06T09:35:59.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eExcept Hammer is so close to radiant (basically editing 3D world in 2D, WTF?), it‚Äôs not even funny.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSomething like Trenchbroom: \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F-1pM55k4WM\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eyoutube.com/watch?v=F-1pM55k4WM\u003c/a\u003e would be more appropriate. Also no, I don‚Äôt have 3ds max, because I don‚Äôt feel like wasting $5000\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:34.059Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":23.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":971,"topic_slug":"bsp-like-level-editing","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F-1pM55k4WM","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"TrenchBroom Quake Level Editor - YouTube","clicks":21}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":227,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":5688,"name":"","username":"GoogleBot42","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/googlebot42/{size}/62_2.png","created_at":"2015-04-07T02:23:55.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n Sinoid:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo why don‚Äôt you fork Trenchbroom and add export straight to Urho?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eJust what I was thinking.  I have no need for this at all so I won‚Äôt make a port.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n Sinoid:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAutodesk throws discounts around like candy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLol.   \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/laughing.png?v=5\" title=\":laughing:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":laughing:\"\u003e   If you are a student you can even get it for free (but not for commercial applications of course).\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:35.153Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":29.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":971,"topic_slug":"bsp-like-level-editing","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":197,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":5715,"name":"","username":"Enhex","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/enhex/{size}/81_2.png","created_at":"2015-04-09T12:31:32.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI also wanted a BSP-like level editor and I made a generic one (that can be used with any game for any game engine).\u003cbr\u003e\nIt‚Äôs still early in development but the basic features already exist.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere‚Äôs the last, outdated, video I uploaded of it:\u003cbr\u003e\n[video]\u003ca href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zbjwM6aztzc%5B/video%5D\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ehttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zbjwM6aztzc[/video]\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBack then I didn‚Äôt use Urho yet, tho when I switched to urho it took few hours to make level loading code.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRight now it export levels as JSON (so you can pick up a lib and parse it with any language).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"darkhog\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/d/b487fb/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e darkhog:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExcept Hammer is so close to radiant (basically editing 3D world in 2D, WTF?), it‚Äôs not even funny.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYour screen is 2D.\u003cbr\u003e\nHaving 2D grids give you more precision and speed. You don‚Äôt have to move a camera around to access stuff.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:37.088Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":19,"readers_count":18,"score":23.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":971,"topic_slug":"bsp-like-level-editing","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zbjwM6aztzc%5B/video%5D","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Level Editor v0.2 Demo","clicks":26}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":184,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6102,"name":"","username":"friesencr","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/friesencr/{size}/827_2.png","created_at":"2015-05-12T05:52:40.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI am going to be trying to do a glsl shader soon that does texture atlas w/ wrapping.  Hopefully it goes well.  I wrote the sprite packer, its urhos sprite packer so we can make it do whatever crap we want.  If you need any features in it let me know.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:07.017Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":4.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":971,"topic_slug":"bsp-like-level-editing","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":15,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6104,"name":"","username":"GoogleBot42","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/googlebot42/{size}/62_2.png","created_at":"2015-05-12T17:23:57.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/friesencr/40/827_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e friesencr:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am going to be trying to do a glsl shader soon that does texture atlas w/ wrapping.  Hopefully it g